This collection consists of the papers of W. Nathaniel Howell, a career Foreign Service Officer and expert in Middle Eastern affairs, ca. 1947-2001, ca. 2,150 items (6 Hollinger boxes and 2 cubics, ca. 4 linear
shelf feet). Materials include an appointment desk diary; correspondence; research material concerning the Kurds, which includes related material on the history of Iraq, the Soviet Union, and the Baath Party;
memorabilia and papers pertaining to Howell's high school and college education; news clippings; and photographs.
